hakoniwa-core (1.2.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  [ Takashi Mori ]
  * New upstream release v1.2.0.
  * Add Godot-related PDU definitions in hakoniwa-pdu-registry.
  * Add PowerShell-based Windows build/install scripts and document the
    Windows build workflow in README.md.
  * Centralize build-time capacity defaults in
    cmake/hako_build_defaults.conf and apply them across CMake, build.bash,
    install.bash, and Windows build scripts.
  * Add build/install-time overrides for service/client name length limits:
    HAKO_CLIENT_NAMELEN_MAX and HAKO_SERVICE_NAMELEN_MAX.
  * Add APIs to attach asset endpoints to the core without registration and
    improve polling/callback asset initialization for external use cases.
  * Fix compact robot/PDU parsing to avoid stale entries and improve
    duplicate-channel detection by using channel size in the uniqueness key.
  * Improve polling/callback API robustness with lazy controller
    initialization, safer exception handling, and additional build-limit /
    shared-memory size logs.
  * Fix Windows build issues, including MuJoCo-related compilation failures
    and script/build configuration regressions.

 -- Takashi Mori <tmori@hakoniwa-lab.net>  Tue, 05 May 2026 08:26:17 +0900

hakoniwa-core (1.1.4-1) noble; urgency=medium

  [ Takashi Mori ]
  * New upstream release v1.1.4.
  * Add build/install-time PDU channel capacity override:
    CHANNEL_MAX / HAKO_PDU_CHANNEL_MAX.
  * Add service client channel lookup API by concrete handle and update
    Python binding to use (service_id, client_id).
  * Improve concurrent access handling for service metadata and recv-event
    tables with additional locking and indexed lookup.
  * Serialize service and callback-side PDU channel creation to reduce
    multi-process startup races.
  * Add pro_init.lock handling for PDU shared-memory create/load paths.
  * Document lock ordering rules for fleet startup scenarios.
  * Update hakoniwa-core-cpp submodule (00ccc22 -> c41e551; fixes #55, #56).

 -- Takashi Mori <tmori@hakoniwa-lab.net>  Sat, 14 Mar 2026 08:11:40 +0900

hakoniwa-core (1.1.3-1) noble; urgency=medium

  [ Takashi Mori ]
  * New upstream release v1.1.3.
  * Add build/install-time capacity overrides:
    HAKO_SERVICE_MAX, HAKO_RECV_EVENT_MAX, HAKO_SERVICE_CLIENT_MAX.
  * Extend build scripts with capacity environment variables and larger defaults:
    ASSET_NUM (4->16), SERVICE_MAX, RECV_EVENT_MAX, SERVICE_CLIENT_MAX.
  * Apply asset_timeout_usec consistently in init/controller paths and add logs.
  * Fix service protocol polling interval handling.
  * Fix polling client lookup collisions by using (service_id, client_id) keys.
  * Improve recovery from stale shared-memory service metadata.
  * Fix Windows test build issue for environment variable setup.
  * Update submodules:
    hakoniwa-core-cpp (7d419d6->00ccc22),
    hakoniwa-pdu-registry (d447116->8f31bcd).

 -- Takashi Mori <tmori@hakoniwa-lab.net>  Mon, 09 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0900

hakoniwa-core (1.1.2-1) noble; urgency=medium

  [ Takashi Mori ]
  * New upstream release v1.1.2.
  * Add new polling-based Hakoniwa C API.
  * Add APIs to retrieve minimum asset simulation time.
  * Add on-demand PDU data loading API.
  * Extend data receive event notification functionality.
  * Reduce excessive WARNING logs for busy data receive events.
  * Fix missing data receive events in some cases.
  * Fix duplicate function names between hako_capi.h and hako_asset.h.
  * Fix incorrect return type of hako_conductor_start().
  * Update PDU definition system:
    - Rename hakoniwa-ros2pdu to hakoniwa-pdu-registry.
    - Support new PDU definition format compatible with custom.json.
  * Fix Linux build issue in build.bash.
  * Fix python3-hakopy package installation (hakopy.so missing).
  * Add Python API to retrieve asset simulation time.

 -- Code <tmori@hakoniwa-lab.net>  Mon, 02 Feb 2026 08:52:17 +0900

